{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[G3 child-coverage audit — parent 72d5 (Migrate the LLM gates onto the workflow engine) vs child B-RETIRE (retire the parity harness + the bespoke plan-review path once parity is exhaustively validated)] Clean — no findings.\n\n4-bucket audit of the parent's acceptance/success criteria against THIS child, with whole-roster absence cross-check:\n\n- Parent AC4 (the bespoke orchestrator path is cut over to the workflow path BEHIND THE GATE(S) once parity holds; the close/claim gates keep working — signed verdicts/attestations intact): PARTIALLY covered by this child, as its terminal step. B5 (f12d) performs the cutover + leaves the bespoke path reachable behind verify.gate_engine as a fallback; B-RETIRE removes that fallback flag + the bespoke `orchestrator.run_review` path + the ThreadPoolExecutor fan-out so the engine workflow becomes the SOLE plan-review gate, while its AC (\"review_plan library/CLI/MCP entrypoints still work; forwarding shims preserved; close/claim gates keep working through the workflow path with signatures intact\") faithfully mirrors AC4's \"keep working / signed verdicts/attestations intact\" clause. The remainder of AC4 (the cutover itself, default-to-workflow, byte-compatible signing) is FULLY covered by siblings B5 (f12d) + 0408. No gap — AC4 is fully covered across the roster.\n\n- Parent AC3 (planned-trace parity harness, offline FakeRunner, CI): FULLY covered by sibling B4 (101a). B-RETIRE consumes/retires it (removes test_plan_review_parity.py + _parity_corpus.py + unused TracingFakeRunner) only AFTER exhaustive validation; this is consistent removal of migration scaffolding, not a coverage contribution. Its precondition AC (\"parity recorded as exhaustively validated — comprehensive corpus + documented soak with the workflow as the sole live gate, no regression — BEFORE any deletion\") guards the removal, consistent with the parent's \"once parity holds\" gating.\n\n- Parent AC1 (plan-review as engine workflow + production batch-runner extracted from sizing.py): not-this-child — FULLY covered by B2 (6b06) + B1 (723c). B-RETIRE explicitly PRESERVES the shared machinery the workflow still uses (pass1.run_pass1, det_floor, registry, passes, sizing, attest, ProductionBatchRunner), so it does not regress AC1.\n\n- Parent AC2 (verify_completion as engine workflow, existing step kinds): not-this-child — FULLY covered by B3 (dc58). (Note: B-RETIRE scopes itself to the plan-review path + parity harness only; it does not touch completion-verification, which is internally consistent with the simpler B3 migration leaving no bespoke-vs-workflow dual harness to retire for that gate.)\n\n- Parent AC5 (remove throwaway sample stubs; preserve shims; retain epic-A demo): not-this-child — FULLY covered by B6 (7e48).\n\n- Parent AC6 / Success criterion (exactly two real LLM workflows + the one retained sample; only real workflows remain; make lint + full suite pass): primarily covered by B6 (7e48); B-RETIRE contributes its own \"no orphaned references to the removed code; make lint + full test suite pass\" AC, reinforcing the lint/test-green portion.\n\n- Parent success criterion (\"plan-review and completion-verification run on the ONE workflow-engine substrate ... validated by offline planned-trace parity against the bespoke implementations; only real workflows remain\"): the cross-roster union (B1/B2/B3/B4/B5/0408 + B-DM 5506) covers the substrate/prompt-library/parity halves; B-RETIRE provides convergence (removing the now-dead second implementation + harness) so that, post-epic, exactly ONE plan-review gate remains — the natural end-state of \"convergence: only what earns its keep remains.\"\n\nWhole-roster absence cross-check: every parent acceptance/success criterion is covered by at least one child in the complete sibling roster; no parent criterion is left uncovered, and B-RETIRE introduces no new uncovered parent criterion. The ordering (B-RETIRE's \"FINAL convergence step; must come AFTER B5 and after parity is exhaustively validated\") is consistent with parent AC3/AC4 sequencing and with the deps (f12d blocks 961b). No G3 finding."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782507873640236001,"uuid":"213b52c1-da2b-494d-9368-db6ecfb80f52"}